commit.message: Update copyright statement in the README.
Update version number to 4.1
Add test `parsebib-clean-TeX-markup-nested-macros`.

parsebib-clean-TeX-markup: allow commands in arguments of formatting commands.

Don't interpret backslash special if replacement is a function. This should fix
Github issue #22.

Revert "Move formatting commands to the end of `parsebib-TeX-markup-replacement-alist`."

This reverts commit 363df0ba0e51e97709fc2ecb9bb9ad9db7b8d84f.

Move formatting commands to the end of `parsebib-TeX-markup-replacement-alist`.

This is a workaround for Github issue #22.
Remove test code.

Correctly match `\\$` in parsebib-clean-TeX-markup.

For some reason, the string `"\\$"` would not be matched by
`parsebib-clean-TeX-markup`, although `"\\$ "` (note the extra space) would.
This commit ensures that both are matched correctly.
Untabify parsebib.el

Add `parsebib-clean-TeX-markup`.

Include the functionality to make TeX markup suitable for display, which was
formerly included in Ebib, into parsebib. This makes this functionality
available for other packages using parsebib.
Declare the function `json-read`.
Update copyright statement.

commit.message: `parsebib--get-xref-fields`: use all matching biblatex rules

Use `none` in `parsebib--biblatex-inheritances`.

In order to resolve issue
[#231](https://github.com/joostkremers/ebib/issues/231) in Ebib, the formats of
`parsebib--biblatex-inheritances` and `ebib-biblatex-inheritances` need to be
synchronised. Using keywords somehow feels less Elisp-y, and the Ebib version is
user-customisable, where a plain symbol may be more user-friendly.
Update copyright statement.
